verbose_text: We noted that fluoride had little effect on osteoclatogenesis; this result was similar to that of our previous study; the number of OCs (> 3 nuclei) or the number of giant OCs (> 20 nuclei) in mice in the F + TP group was greater than that in the F group on day 3, suggesting that TPs promoted osteoclastogenesis in association with exposure to high levels of fluoride.
